spans.text: hear her , conscious of her Fate , With fearful Groans , and hideous Cries , Fill the presaging Skies
Those dismal Harbingers of dire Events !
Those dismal Harbingers of dire Events !
By Wars , and Pestilence , and Dearth , Through the whole mournful Earth
in the universal tumult , all destroy
Cities fly For safety to their Champion Ground
the Burnings of the thirsty Field
the Deep it self is not secure
neither Earth , nor Air , nor Water
neither Earth , nor Air , nor Water
neither Earth , nor Air , nor Water
if a purple Flood , Overflowed her tottering Orb
Like a huge mass of black corrupting Blood
every Region of the tortured Earth and Air
At whose amazing Sound , fresh Agonies
For now she'll in few Minutes
For now she'll in few Minutes
the silent Grave's dark Chambers lay
many Years before , Though through strange Accidents and numerous Changes
how the joyful Angels fly From every Quarter of the Sky , To gather
what tenderness and love they bear Those righteous Souls through the tumultuous Air
OH Horror , Curses , Tortures , Chains , they cry , And roar aloud with execrable Blasphemy
concealed , if possible , for ever there
it's better , if Heaven would give consent , To have no Being
OH inexpressible stupendous Punishment , Which cannot be endured , yet
to the Sublunary World his Passage bends
The cursed Refuse of Mankind , and Hell's proud Seed
most High , In sacred Discipline and Order
Whose Souls abhorring all ignoble Crimes

Death adore , For whom such Torments and such Pains they bore , Returns to place them on those Thrones above , Where undisturbed , uncloyed , they will possess Divine substantial Happiness , Unbounded as his Power , and lasting as his Love

Whom neither threat , nor promises could move , Not all my Sufferings
Swifter than Lightning , or the swiftest thought , And less than in an instant brought , The wretched , cursed infernal Crew , Who with distorted Aspects come , To hear their sad intolerable Doom
At this ten Millions of Archangels
them not extend to all Eternity
does no place remain For penitence , and tears
first the Virtuous , and the Good , Who all the Fury of Temptation stood , And bravely passed through Ignominy , Chains and Blood ; Attended by their Guardian Angels
In vain the grand Accuser , railing
A long Indictment of enormous Things , Whose Guilt wiped off by penitential Tears
the secret Womb of dark Oblivion
you by my Eternal Father made , Ever the Foundation of the World was laid
Ever the Foundation of the World
Ever the Foundation of the World
lay , Naked and starved almost for want of Bread , You did your kindly Visits pay , Both clothed my Body , and my Hunger fed
your kindly Visits pay , Both clothed my Body , and my Hunger fed
Wearied with Sickness , or oppressed with Grief , Your hand
to supply : Whenever I wanted , you were always by , To share my Sorrows , or to give Relief
No black Misfortune , or vexatious Care
No black Misfortune , or vexatious Care
was thy self , and will for ever be
Therefore all Glory , Power , Dominion , Majesty , To thee , OH Lamb of God , to thee , For ever , longer than for ever be
his Face To those upon the Left
Prepared for those Rebellious Sons of Light
a dreadful Cloud , Enclosing all the miserable Crowd , A mighty Hurricane of Thunder
a Lake of Fire , Which never , never , never can expire : The vast Abyss of endless Woes
